 <br>
nothing else has the sheer amount of tools for pulling exp mobs and there's always the panic button of fade to live and no wipe the group.<br>
<br>
There's 3 basic tools we get that set us apart.... bellow aa, lull and move while cast. If a monk needs to fd, they are wasting time, they get a compareable lull now but it's still not as flexible. Moving while casting is so major it's hard to play my wee necro....<br>
<br>
That said tho which is more usful for the group? the bard staying in group for mana and overhaste (assuming haste is click) and a melee pulling in exp, or the bard being out of camp most of the time pulling so mobs are always in camp?<br>
<br>
I often find myself hving to sit on my hands when I let other people pull cause most are just too damn slow. Thankfully we got a ton of pullaholics around currently so even the cleric's two boxed sk is running around 24/7.<br>
<br>
Pulling exp tho is not what's at stake.... raid pulls are the issue and fd is worth the wait.<br>
<br>
